posts.name: Gus Michel II
posts.cooked:
At least two years, 3946 used ‚Äúliquid electrical tape‚Äù for main breaker and new/re-done battery connections.  Here‚Äôs an example in black:

Introducing STAR BRITE Liquid Electrical Tape 32 Ounce, also available in both 4-ounce cans and 1-ounce tubes, designed to meet all your electrical sealing needs. Superior to electrical tape, it adheres to metal, plastic, vinyl, rubber, and composite...

Our electrical lead mentor purchased a can of red and a can of black.  By year three or four it gummed up, so only buy 1 or 2 years‚Äô worth at a time. Note : this is something you want to apply outdoors, under a chemical hood, or other nearly as powerful air circulation from outdoors to outdoors.  In our case, we applied this outdoors, usually under covered walkways and landings because precipitation is possible most days. Here in Southeast Louisiana, we always had a reasonable number of days with outdoor temperatures suitable for curing during build season.  YMMV mostly by latitude.
